stdin
  ↓
BoardParser         → produces Board
BoardValidator      → validates Board
  ↓
Game                → holds Board + RealTimeArbiter + RuleEngine
  ↓
CommandParser       → parses lines into Command objects
  ↓
for each Command:
  ├── ClickCommand  → InputController.on_click(x, y, game)
  │     ↓
  │   BoardMapper   → converts pixels to cell (row, col)
  │     ↓
  │   InputController → manages selection state
  │     └── game.request_move(piece, start, end)
  │           ↓
  │         RuleEngine → is_legal_move? (delegates to MovementStrategy)
  │           ↓
  │         RealTimeArbiter.add_move(piece, start, end, finish_time)
  │
  ├── WaitCommand   → game.advance_time(ms)
  │     ↓
  │   RealTimeArbiter.advance(current_time, board)
  │     → resolves finished motions
  │     → returns (captured, applied_moves)
  │     ↓
  │   Game._process_captures → sets game_over if royal captured
  │   Game._process_arrivals → calls strategy.on_arrival (e.g. promotion)
  │
  └── PrintBoardCommand → game.snapshot()
        ↓
      BoardPrinter.render(snapshot)
        ↓
      stdout


